               <residence><placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar"> Gondar</placeName></residence>
         
              <floruit > He was a member of the Gondarine court and the royal chronicler. He also belonged to the higher clergy in the court of Gondarine rulers. Intially,
                 he was the azzāž (official to administer court activities) in the court of King  <persName ref="PRS10375Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs I</persName> and
                  towards the end of the reign of King <persName ref="PRS10375Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs I</persName> he was granted the title of ṣaḥāfe tǝʿǝzāz. 
                 He was the author of <title ref="LIT3947ChronYohannes">Chronicle of Yohannǝs I</title>and also partly the  <title ref="LIT3950ChronIyasu">Chronicle of Iyāsu I</title> 
                 
               </floruit>
               <death > He died in <date>04-05-1700</date>. He was killed in a battle between the royal army and the warriors of the Oromo Gudru. </death>
               
            </person>
